        Verbs and Verbal Phrases
      </h2>
      <h3 class='article'>
        <a name="verbal"></a>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9256' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'dòngcí', 'verb')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">动词</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1347' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'xìng', 'sex / nature / surname / suffix corresponding to -ness')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">性</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9257' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cízǔ', 'phrase')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">词组</a>
        Verbal Phrases
      </h3>
      <p>
        In verbal sentences the comment has a verb.  Verbs may be transitive or intransitive.  
        Transitive verbs take an object. For example,
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3896' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'to know / to be aware')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">知</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1574' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'qí', 'his / her / its / theirs / that')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">其</a>
        (knew it).  Intransitive do not take an object.  For example,
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=4467' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'dào', 'a thief / a bandit')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>盗</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17159' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'wáng', 'to leave / to flee')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>亡</a> 
        (the thief fled).
      <p>
      </p>
        An adjective describes a quality or continuing state of an object and are sometimes
        classified as stative verbs because they can form predicates.  For example,
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3122' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shān', 'mountain / hill')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">山</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=953' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'gāo', 'high / tall')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">高</a>
        (The mountain is tall).  However, adjectives are more commonly found in front of nouns
        as modifiers.  For example,
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1187' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'fù', 'rich')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">富</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=399' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'rén', 'person / people')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">人</a>
        (a rich person).  
      </p>
      <p>
        Adjectives can also be made into transitive verbs by moving the subject to the 
        object position.  For example
      </p>
      <p class='example'>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3236' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'wáng', 'king / prince')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>王</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=279' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'qǐng', 'to ask / to invite / please')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>请</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1114' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'dà', 'big / huge / large / major')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>大</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=730' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'him / her / it')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>之</a><br/>
        I plead with Your Majesty to make it large
      </p>
